  "text": "Furthermore, it is observed that as the number of PP codes phases is increased the performance is enhanced providing a gain of up to 2.5 dB when (φ = 8), compared to OFDM, at CCDF = 10 −3 . This can be intuitively justified by the increase in the phase randomization across the sub-carriers which is related to the minimum-distance decoding of the sequences [CITATION_1] . This, eventually, leads to more averaging of the transmitted MC-CDMA signal and, consequently, improves the overall PAPR performance. As a result, better probability of blanking error can be achieved, i.e. more efficient noise suppression can be accomplished as shown below.",
